text: Coesfeld is a town in North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany and the capital of Coesfeld county. Nepomucenum and St.-Pius-Gymnasium are highschools in Coesfeld. == History == Coesfeld was founded by the holy Ludgerus. Coesfeld has been a town since 1197.
